# Documentation Standards

## Single Source of Truth for Schemas

All content collection schemas must be defined in [docs/schemas.md](mdc:docs/schemas.md). Never duplicate schema definitions in other documentation files.

### Schema References
- **Episodes Collection**: See [docs/schemas.md](mdc:docs/schemas.md) for complete episode schema
- **Guests Collection**: See [docs/schemas.md](mdc:docs/schemas.md) for complete guest schema
- **Media Files**: See [docs/schemas.md](mdc:docs/schemas.md) for media file requirements

### Documentation Structure
- [docs/index.md](mdc:docs/index.md) - High-level overview and quick start
- [docs/schemas.md](mdc:docs/schemas.md) - Single source of truth for all schemas
- [docs/content-collections-user-guide.md](mdc:docs/content-collections-user-guide.md) - Usage instructions
- [docs/content-collections-implementation.md](mdc:docs/content-collections-implementation.md) - Technical details

### Rules
1. **Never duplicate schema definitions** - Always link to [docs/schemas.md](mdc:docs/schemas.md)
2. **Update schemas in one place** - Only modify [docs/schemas.md](mdc:docs/schemas.md) for schema changes
3. **Keep implementation in sync** - Ensure [src/content.config.ts](mdc:src/content.config.ts) matches schema documentation
4. **Use cross-references** - Link between documentation files instead of duplicating content
